nthly reconciliations of all bitcoin wallets including: coding, classifying, and verifying transactions. Enter approved month-end and year-end entries to assist in closing the books and records. Create profitability models for new products, features, and ventures within the company. Monitor department specific budges. Perform other duties as assigned. Basic Qualifications: Minimum of 2 years of experience as a bookkeeper, accountant, or other relatable experience. Bachelor\u2019s degree in Finance, Accounting, or related field. Ability to work in a fast paced environment, handle ambiguity, and shifting priorities. Mastery with Microsoft Excel, QuickBooks, and other financial tools. An understanding of how the Bitcoin network operates. Preferred Qualifications: Experience working in cryptocurrency industry in a relevant role. Enterprise experience. Perks: Accessible office in the Financial District Flexible hours Competitive salary, with the option of payment in bitcoin Premium covered healthcare insurance, including dental and vision Catered lunch and dinner daily Gym membership of your choice Sponsored sports nutrition and health-related activities Paid maternity/paternity leave including a special one-time bonus to support newborn Commuter benefits Training and professional development resources Paid company retreats Skills accounting, finance Compensation 60000-70000 Applications for this job are currently closed. ",
